    "body": "## Summary\n- Reverts #13006 (which reverted #12062) to re-enable EAGLE3 dynamic tree speculative decoding support\n- Cherry-picks the fix from #13000 to disable spec decoding variable on Blackwell (trtllmGen FMHA kernels do not yet support spec decoding mode)\n\n## Changes\n- Restores all EAGLE3 dynamic tree kernel code (`dynamicTreeKernels.cu/h`, `dynamicTreeOp.cpp`)\n- Restores Python dynamic tree implementation (`dynamic_tree_ops.py`, `eagle3_dynamic_tree.py`)\n- Restores attention backend changes for spec decoding tree support\n- Restores spec tree manager, drafting loop, and eagle3 model changes\n- Restores documentation and example updates\n- Restores unit tests for dynamic tree functionality\n- Adds Blackwell guard: disables `is_spec_decoding_enabled` on sm100+ GPUs\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] CI passes on Hopper (H100) with EAGLE3 dynamic tree tests\n- [x] Verify spec decoding is correctly disabled on Blackwell (B200/GB200)\n- [x] Unit tests: `test_eagle3.py`, `test_kv_cache_update.py`, `test_custom_ops.py`\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added dynamic tree mode for EAGLE-3 speculative decoding with configurable top-K branching and draft token limits.\n  * Extended `Eagle3DecodingConfig` with `use_dynamic_tree`, `dynamic_tree_max_topK`, `max_total_draft_tokens`, and `max_batch_size` parameters.\n  * Enhanced examples with accept rate metrics and streaming generation support.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Updated feature matrix to distinguish EAGLE-3 linear and dynamic tree modes.\n  * Added dynamic tree configuration guide with constraints and limitations.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
